// This strategy uses Noro Trendribbon side change to know if the positions need to be long and short.
// In addition to the former a corridor is defined using high and low prices from latest candles.
// When the price is below that corridor (and we are longing) a long position is open with a certain percentage of the usual corridor.
// When the price is above that corridor (and we are shorting) a short position is open with a certain percentage of the usual corridor.
// Fast EMAs levels are used as a way to close the trades.
// This specific strategy also includes Risk Management.
// 
// It was originally tested at 1000SHIBUSDT pair and 30m timeframe.
//
